</span></p><p class="sc-lnPyOc exfzrW pf-19_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fThTNe cAYhcc pf-21_">“Is there really a difference between statutory and mandatory training?”</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ggpkNl jdwwxc pf-22_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fThTNe cAYhcc pf-24_">What is the difference between statutory and mandatory training?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/pexelsekaterinabolovtsova6077326-1671779620993.jpg?v=1671779630" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/pexelsekaterinabolovtsova6077326-1671779620993.jpg?v=1671779630 1536w" width="5472" height="3648" alt="Is there a difference between mandatory and statutory training? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Is there a difference between mandatory and statutory training? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-sLtfs jkHPMQ pf-25_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-lnPyOc exfzrW pf-26_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fThTNe cAYhcc pf-28_">Admittedly, the words ‘mandatory’ and ‘statutory’ have similarities but also significant differences, especially regarding compliance training, such as health and safety at work training.
<br><br>
We looked at various dictionaries to see how they define "statutory" and "mandatory". We also reviewed several compliance-related websites and found that ‘mandatory’ and ‘statutory’ are used interchangeably as if they mean the same thing. What was clear was that statutory training is mandatory, while mandatory training is not necessarily statutory.
<br><br>
